com.sri.ai.grinder.polynomial.core

Class MonomialComparator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sri.ai.grinder.polynomial.core.MonomialSignatureComparator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparator<Monomial>

    @Beta
public class MonomialComparator
extends Object
implements Comparator<Monomial>
    A monomial M1 comes before another monomial M2 if it has higher degree or if their degree are the same wrt to a tuple of factors F iff signature(M1, F) is lexicographically larger than signature(M2, F). For example:

    x^3 comes before x^2

    Author:
    oreilly
